    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains univariate time-series data (12 monthly observations) with synthetic values simulating commercial energy consumption. Synthetic data (\u03bc=500 kWh, \u03c3=100 kWh) incorporates two statistical properties: 1) Quadratic seasonal trend peaking in summer months (June-July), 2) Normally distributed residuals around the trend line. The column chart format was selected based on Tufte's data-ink principles - direct comparison of discrete categories benefits from clear baseline alignment and proportional encoding. Cairo's perceptual topology is maintained through consistent color gradients and y-axis zero-baseline. Chart colors (#1abc9c \u2192 #16a085) follow WCAG contrast standards while supporting intuitive magnitude comparisons through value saturation gradients."
